# local.zsh.example — template for your Secret Profile's environment variables
#
# This file is a plaintext TEMPLATE. It is NOT deployed to ~/.config/zsh/local.zsh directly.
# The deployed local.zsh is generated by decrypting your profile's local.zsh.age secret.
#
# Workflow to populate a new profile's secrets:
#   1. Copy this file and fill in your real values (do NOT commit the plaintext copy)
#   2. Encrypt it:  age -r <your-pubkey> -o secrets/profiles/<profile>/local.zsh.age local.zsh
#   3. Commit only the .age file; delete the plaintext copy
#
# Example contents:
#   export GITHUB_TOKEN="ghp_..."
#   export B2_KEY="..."
#   export PULUMI_ACCESS_TOKEN="pul-..."
